cs.SE, cs.HC, cs.SD, cs.PL, cs.CY

Reasoning: 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is the most likely category as the paper investigates the perceptions and attitudes of developers towards agile development practices in Scrum software development teams. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is also likely as the paper discusses the impact of team culture and collaboration on software development practices. 
- cs.SD (Software Development) is relevant as the paper focuses on the usage of agile development practices in software development teams. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is relevant as the paper discusses the usage of version control systems and Test-Driven Development. 
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is less likely but still possible as the paper touches on the social and cultural aspects of software development teams.
